      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How is property split during a divorce in Australia?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Property settlements in Australia are not necessarily 50/50. The Family Court considers contributions made by each party (financial and non-financial), future needs, and the overall justice of the settlement. The starting point is an assessment of the total property pool, which is why a current market appraisal is one of the first practical steps in the process."
